question: In which department is Ms. Brant?
query:
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>

PREFIX dbo: <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/>
PREFIX dbr: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/>
PREFIX pv: <http://ld.company.org/prod-vocab/>
SELECT ?department WHERE { 
  ?agent a pv:Agent ;
         pv:name ?agentName ;
         pv:memberOf ?department .

}

question: What is the cheapest Encoder we can get from a french or german supplier?
query:
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/>
PREFIX schema: <http://schema.org/>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX ecc: <https://ns.eccenca.com/>
PREFIX void: <http://rdfs.org/ns/void#>
PREFIX vann: <http://purl.org/vocab/vann/>
PREFIX dbp: <http://dbpedia.org/property/>
PREFIX dbo: <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/>
PREFIX dbr: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/>
PREFIX pv: <http://ld.company.org/prod-vocab/>
PREFIX prodi: <http://ld.company.org/prod-instances/>

SELECT ?encoder ?priceAmount WHERE {
    ?encoder a pv:Hardware ;
        pv:hasCategory prodi:encoderCategory ;
        pv:price ?price ;
        pv:hasSupplier ?supplier .
        
    ?price pv:amount ?priceAmount ;
        pv:currency "EUR" .
        
    ?supplier pv:addressCountry ?country .
    FILTER (?country = "France" || ?country = "Germany")
}
ORDER BY ASC(?priceAmount)
LIMIT 1

question: What is the pontiometer with the smallest volume?

PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/>

PREFIX dbo: <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/>
PREFIX dbr: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/>
PREFIX pv: <http://ld.company.org/prod-vocab/>
SELECT ?pontiometer ?minVolume WHERE { 
    ?pontiometer a pv:Hardware ; 
                  pv:width_mm ?width ; 
                  pv:height_mm ?height ; 
                  pv:depth_mm ?depth .
    BIND(?width * ?height * ?depth AS ?volume)
} ORDER BY ?volume
LIMIT 1

question: Which coil has the highest density?
query:
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>

SELECT ?coil ?maxDensity
WHERE { 
    ?coil a pv:Product ;                # Assuming pv:Product is the category for coils
          rdfs:label ?label ;           # Consider all products with a label
          pv:density ?density .         # Assume there is a density property

}
ORDER BY DESC(?density)
LIMIT 1

question: What suppliers - I need name, country and price - deliver the 6th to 10th most expensive hardware items.
query:

PREFIX foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/>

PREFIX dbr: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/>

SELECT ?supplier ?supplierName ?supplierCountry ?hardware ?priceAmount
WHERE { 
    {
        SELECT ?hardware ?priceAmount
        WHERE { 
            ?hardware a pv:Hardware ; 
                      pv:price ?price . 
            ?price pv:amount ?priceAmount ; 
                   pv:currency "EUR" . 
        }
        ORDER BY DESC(?priceAmount)
        OFFSET 5
        LIMIT 5
    }

    ?hardware pv:hasSupplier ?supplier .
    ?supplier pv:name ?supplierName ;
              pv:country ?country .
    ?country rdfs:label ?supplierCountry .
}
ORDER BY DESC(?priceAmount)

question: Which department have more than 5 employees? I need their names and the number of employees.

question: I need to update my supplier rolodex, give me every supplier's name and all address details.
For every product, list what other products it is compatible with and the price differences between both.
query:
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/>
PREFIX schema: <http://schema.org/>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX ecc: <https://ns.eccenca.com/>
PREFIX void: <http://rdfs.org/ns/void#>
PREFIX vann: <http://purl.org/vocab/vann/>
PREFIX dbp: <http://dbpedia.org/property/>
PREFIX dbo: <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/>
PREFIX dbr: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/>
PREFIX pv: <http://ld.company.org/prod-vocab/>
PREFIX prodi: <http://ld.company.org/prod-instances/>

SELECT ?product ?compatibleProduct ?priceDiff
WHERE { 
  ?product a pv:Product ;
           pv:compatibleProduct ?compatibleProduct ;
           pv:price ?prodPrice .
  ?prodPrice pv:amount ?productPriceAmount .

  ?compatibleProduct pv:price ?compPrice .
  ?compPrice pv:amount ?compProductPriceAmount .

  BIND(abs(?productPriceAmount - ?compProductPriceAmount) AS ?priceDiff)
}

question: For each Bill of Material, how many parts does it contain and what is the total material quantity — show me only those BOMs exceeding 600 total items and order them descending.

PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>

PREFIX foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/>
PREFIX schema: <http://schema.org/>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>

PREFIX void: <http://rdfs.org/ns/void#>
PREFIX vann: <http://purl.org/vocab/vann/>
PREFIX dbp: <http://dbpedia.org/property/>
PREFIX dbo: <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/>
PREFIX dbr: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/>
PREFIX pv: <http://ld.company.org/prod-vocab/>

SELECT ?bom (COUNT(?bomPart) AS ?numberOfParts) (SUM(?quantity) AS ?totalMaterialQuantity)
WHERE {
  ?bom a pv:BillOfMaterial ;
       pv:hasBomPart ?bomPart .
  ?bomPart pv:quantity ?quantity .
}
GROUP BY ?bom
HAVING (SUM(?quantity) > 600)
ORDER BY DESC(?totalMaterialQuantity)

PREFIX pv: <http://ld.company.org/prod-vocab/>
PREFIX dbr: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?bom WHERE {
    ?bom a pv:BillOfMaterial ; 
         pv:hasBomPart ?part .
    ?part a pv:BomPart ; 
          pv:part ?product .
    ?product pv:hasSupplier ?supplier .
    ?supplier pv:country dbr:Poland .
}

question: How many suppliers can deliver alternative compatible products for the K367 Strain Encoder?
query:
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/>
PREFIX schema: <http://schema.org/>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX ecc: <https://ns.eccenca.com/>
PREFIX void: <http://rdfs.org/ns/void#>
PREFIX vann: <http://purl.org/vocab/vann/>
PREFIX dbp: <http://dbpedia.org/property/>
PREFIX dbo: <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/>
PREFIX dbr: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/>
PREFIX pv: <http://ld.company.org/prod-vocab/> 
PREFIX prodi: <http://ld.company.org/prod-instances/> 

SELECT DISTINCT ?compatibleProduct ?supplier
WHERE {
  prodi:yourProductID pv:compatibleProduct ?compatibleProduct .
  ?compatibleProduct pv:hasSupplier ?supplier .
}

question: Which department is resposible for the most product and how many product are this?
query:
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/>
PREFIX schema: <http://schema.org/>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX ecc: <https://ns.eccenca.com/>
PREFIX void: <http://rdfs.org/ns/void#>
PREFIX vann: <http://purl.org/vocab/vann/>
PREFIX dbp: <http://dbpedia.org/property/>
PREFIX dbo: <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/>
PREFIX dbr: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/>
PREFIX pv: <http://ld.company.org/prod-vocab/>
SELECT ?department (COUNT(?product) AS ?productCount)
WHERE { 
    ?department a pv:Department .
    ?department pv:responsibleFor ?product .
}
GROUP BY ?department
ORDER BY DESC(?productCount)
LIMIT 1
